title: Alphaville - 80's Live Collection [2012] DVD5
description: Alphaville - 80's Live Collection [2012] DVD5 Alphaville is a German synthpop/new wave band which gained popularity in the 1980s. The founding members were lead singer Marian Gold (b 26 May 1954 in Herford), Bernhard Lloyd (b 2 June 1960 in Enger), and Frank Mertens (b 26 October 1961 in Enger). They achieved chart success with the singles "Forever Young", "Big in Japan", "Sounds Like a Melody", "Jet Set", "Dance With Me", "Jerusalem", and "Romeos". This is a custom DVD with unofficial collection of some of their live performances on various TV shows from 1984 to 1987.
